    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-04-22T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-04-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="312"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d312">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/4–2249: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-04-22">April 22,
                            1949</date>.<lb/>[Received April 22—7:51 a. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>826. Communist broadcast April 22 announces river crossing starting midnight
                    April 20, smashing Yangtze defense line, built by Kmt<note n="32"
                        xml:id="d312fn32">Kuomintang (Nationalist Party).</note> reactionaries
                    during past 3½ months, like hacking away a lot of dead wood. Enemy troops had no
                    will to fight and fell back in utter confusion. In less than 24 hours 300,000
                        PLA<note n="33" xml:id="d312fn33">People’s Liberation Army
                        (Communist).</note> men completed crossing and wrested away wide areas of
                    south bank including Fanchang, Nanling, Tsingyang, Tikang and other cities,
                    broadcast states.</p>
                <p>Sent Department 826, repeated Shanghai and OffEmb Canton unnumbered.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stuart</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
